# Native alliance — RBAC, invites, and commander claims

Use this rule when changing team invites, onboarding, member-link, or officer tooling. Pair with [`.cursor/rules/invite-commander-identity.mdc`](invite-commander-identity.mdc) for name/UID matching invariants and [`.cursor/rules/player-uid-privacy.mdc`](player-uid-privacy.mdc) for UID display rules.

**Operator guides (maintainer-facing copy lives in markdown, not i18n):**

- [Ashed-sync alliance onboarding](../../docs/guides/ashed-alliance-member-onboarding.md) → `/guides/alliance-onboarding/ashed-sync`
- [Fresh native alliance onboarding](../../docs/guides/fresh-native-alliance-onboarding.md) → `/guides/alliance-onboarding/fresh-native`

---

## Three layers (never conflate)

| Layer | Table | Created when | Answers |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **HQ RBAC** | `alliance_memberships` | Invite accept (`acceptHqInvite`) or manual assign | “What can this HQ user **do** in the app?” (owner, officer, member, viewer, …) |
| **Roster commander** | `alliance_members` | Ashed/sync, video OCR commit, owner-approved roster link, owner cold-start | “Who is on **our roster snapshot**?” (`current_name`, ranks — may lag in-game renames) |
| **Character binding** | `hq_member_links` | Member-link submit or claim confirm | “Which roster commander does **this HQ account** represent?” |

Invite accept **never** creates `alliance_members` or `hq_member_links`. Every native alliance user still passes `/onboard` until linked (`sessionRequiresMemberLink`).

---

## Invite kinds (same `hq_invites` table)

| Invite | `roleName` | `targetAshedMemberId` | Typical use |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Officer / viewer / data_entry invite** | non-`member` | null | Grant HQ permissions; invitee still member-links separately |
| **Generic member invite** | `member` | null | RBAC = member; invitee proves identity via UID on `/onboard` |
| **Commander claim invite** | `member` | set | Same as member invite + **bound roster commander**; confirm step + blocks stray self-service while pending |

Commander claim invites are **not** a separate product — `createHqInvite` with `targetAshedMemberId` (`src/lib/native-alliance/invites.ts`). Bulk claim uses `createHqClaimInvitesBulk` (same shape, batch).

**Do not** expose player UID in invite APIs or officer UI — only `ashed_member_id` (internal) and commander display names.

