## Two alliance entry paths

| Path | `operatingMode` | Roster source | Operator guide |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Ashed-sync** | `ashed` (typical legacy) | Ashed connect + roster sync → `alliance_members` often **full on day one** | [Ashed-sync guide](../../docs/guides/ashed-alliance-member-onboarding.md) |
| **Fresh native** | `native` | Starts **empty**; grows via owner cold-start, owner-approved roster links, video OCR, manual ops | [Fresh native guide](../../docs/guides/fresh-native-alliance-onboarding.md) |

Both paths share: invite → accept → `/onboard` → member link or claim confirm. They differ in **who already appears on the roster** and **how officers should distribute invites**.

### Ashed-sync (full roster import)

- Expect **~100 roster rows** mirrored from Ashed; in-game names may **not** match `current_name` until refresh (renames, stale sync).
- Primary officer job: **link HQ accounts to existing roster slots**, not “add members to the alliance.”
- Prefer **commander claim invites** from Team settings → claim section (or commander profile) for each **unlinked** roster member.
- Generic **member** invite / join code still works but is weaker (no pre-bound commander); use when the officer does not know which roster row yet.
- **Officer / viewer / data_entry** invites remain required for RBAC — claim invites are always `member` role.

### Fresh native (owner-only cold start — e.g. BigD)

- Only the **owner** has HQ access at first; `alliance_members` may be empty or owner-only.
- Owner must **member-link first** (cold-start can adopt game server + create first roster row).
- Then issue **officer** invites; officers link themselves (often **owner approval** or roster miss until roster exists).
- Grow roster (video OCR, owner approval on roster-link requests, sync if Ashed added later).
- Shift to **claim invites** once roster names exist and officers can pick unclaimed commanders.
- **Join codes** optional for broad `member` RBAC enrollment; everyone still completes `/onboard`.

Engineering flow reference (APIs, mermaid): [`docs/guides/native-alliance-onboarding.md`](../../docs/guides/native-alliance-onboarding.md).

